Mexico Stocks: Empresas ICA, Industrias Penoles, Mexichem Fall

-- B y   K a t i a   P o r z e c a n s k i
-- 
2011-10-07T21:18:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/mexico-stocks-america-movil-industrias-penoles-walmex-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:30 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.8 percent to 33,005.09.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA* MM), Mexico’s biggest construction
company, fell 0.1 percent to 15.36 pesos. The company was
downgraded to “equal weight” from “overweight” at Morgan
Stanley.  Grupo Bimbo SAB (BIMBOA MM), the world’s largest bread
maker, fell 1.5 percent to 27.82 pesos. Wheat futures for
December delivery declined 1.4 percent.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, fell 0.3 percent to 546.49 pesos as silver for
December delivery dropped 2.3 percent.  Mexichem SAB (MEXICHEM* MM), the largest maker of plastic
pipes in  Latin America , fell 3.1 percent to 41.10 pesos. The
company forecast that third-quarter sales will rise 22 percent
while  cash flow , known as Ebitda, will gain 2 percent. Mexichem
aims to have annual growth of 20 percent for profit, revenue and
Ebitda, it has said in company presentations.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Porzecanski in New York at 
 kporzecansk1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
